<Infographic
  title="Transduction and quantum frequency conversion"
  description="Transduction shifts a single-photon-level quantum signal between frequency regimes without breaking its quantum state. Two regimes: visible-to-telecom quantum frequency conversion (mature, 30–80 % lab efficiencies) and microwave-to-optical transduction (open, sub-percent quantum-noise-limited efficiencies). The second is the device blocking distributed superconducting quantum computing."
